The OPEC Fund for InternationalDevelopment approved 100,000 dlrs in aid for Ecuador, which wasstruck recently by an earthquake.    The Fund, which was set up by the 13 OPEC (Organization ofPetroleum Exporting Countries) member states to help ThirdWorld development, said in a statement the money would be usedto provide medical supplies for the earthquake victims.    Ecuador, itself a member of OPEC, suffered a major blow toits economy when the earthquake damaged a pipeline carryingcrude oil, its chief export earner. Reuter&#3;